	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001918_0001"><!--pb/@n='29r'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><placeName><geogName type="cataract">Cataracts</geogName></placeName> <date when="1863-05-01">1<hi rend="sup underline">st</hi> May 1863</date></p><!-- Again, should "Cataracts" be feature or region? HB 1/4/12 -->
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My dear <persName><choice><abbr>W.</abbr><expan>Waller</expan></choice></persName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>Whoever sends the 
<lb/>food will man the Galzo
<lb/>if you will not use it 
<lb/>I shall - but I suspect 
<lb/>you misunderstand 
<lb/>the matter - </p>
<lb/><p>If the <persName><term type="occupation">Governor</term></persName> does not 
<lb/><choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice> something more 
<lb/>stiff from his own <orgName><choice><abbr>Gov<hi rend="sup underline">t</hi></abbr><expan>Government</expan></choice></orgName>
<lb/>than from me in the <bibl><placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName><!-- geog: Cape Colony -->
<lb/>papers</bibl> I am mistaken. We
<lb/>would like <persName>Rowley</persName> to say 
<lb/>he on the spot <hi rend="underline">can</hi> say nothing 
<lb/>on the merits. I shall bear 
<lb/>it all myself however 
<lb/>like a <term type="nationality">Briton</term>. Something 
<lb/>will come of it nothing like 
<lb/>kicking up a dust on these 
<lb/>subjects</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001918_0002"><!--pb/@n='29v'--></pb><!-- no text on this page AJS 12/1 -->
			
